{
  "texts": [
    "• To develop a novel optimization technique, IYGSA (improved yellow saddle goatfish algorithm), the modified version of YGSA is used to enhance the prediction efficiency of human motion intentions by resolving the errors in the complicated environment.",
    "• To validate the effectualness of the developed framework over conventional models and various validation measures to verify its prediction performance.Leftover parts of the developed framework are described below.",
    "Section \"Literature survey\" contains literature related to the developed framework.",
    "Section \"Multimodal data-based human motion intention prediction: proposed model and its signal collection details\" details the challenges in the classical techniques and includes the developed mode's significance.",
    "Section \"Development of an adaptive hybrid network for human motion intention prediction\" describes the information about deep learning and heuristic techniques."
  ]
}